==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bluefish
<hw>Blue"fish`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A large voracious fish (<spn>Pomatomus
saitatrix</spn>), of the family <fam>Carangid⟦ae⟧</fam>, valued as a
food fish, and widely distributed on the American coast. On the New
Jersey and Rhode Island coast it is called the <altname>horse
mackerel</altname>, in Virginia <altname>saltwater tailor</altname>, or
<altname>skipjack</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A West Indian fish (<spn>Platyglossus
radiatus</spn>), of the family <fam>Labrid⟦ae⟧</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name is applied locally to other species of fishes;
as the cunner, sea bass, squeteague, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bluegown</ent>⟦br⟧
